## Checklist

Please review and check the following before submitting:

### Code Quality

- [ ] My code follows the project's coding standards and conventions
- [ ] I have run `just lint` and fixed all warnings
- [ ] I have run `just format` to ensure consistent code formatting
- [ ] I have run `just check` and all checks pass

### Testing

- [ ] I have added tests that prove my fix/feature works
- [ ] All existing tests pass (`just test-all`)
- [ ] New and existing unit tests pass locally

### Documentation

- [ ] I have updated the documentation accordingly (if applicable)
- [ ] I have added/updated code comments for complex logic
- [ ] I have updated configuration examples (if config changes were made)

### Git Practices

- [ ] My commits follow the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) specification
- [ ] I have rebased my branch on the latest `main` branch
- [ ] I have resolved all merge conflicts
- [ ] Commit messages are clear and descriptive

### Platform Compatibility (if applicable)

- [ ] Changes work on Windows
- [ ] Changes work on macOS
- [ ] Changes work on Linux
- [ ] Or: Changes are platform-specific and documented as such
